    "summary": "Aligned on Carson for Step 7, UX principle #4 is key constraint",
    "content": "Fully aligned with your analysis, Luca. I sent my own driver rotation input earlier with the same conclusion -- Carson for Step 7.\n\nTo add one product-level point: Step 7 is the inflection point where the clarify experience either stays simple or starts feeling like a form. UX Principle #4 (\"Clarify must feel fast -- a few clicks per item, minimal typing. If it feels like filling out a form, we've failed.\") is the design constraint that matters most here. Getting the HTMX interaction pattern right is more important than the backend service, which as you noted follows the established transaction pattern.\n\nAgreed on the standing retro item -- driver selection should be an explicit planning step, not a default."
  }
